    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-29T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-29T02:00:00-05:00" n="320"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2221: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-29T16:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 29, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 29—8:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1342. The following official statement was released to the press by the
                    Information Board at 2:30 p.m. today: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Ambassador Nomura called on the American President on August 28 and in
                            view of the international conditions of the time he delivered, in the
                            form of a message from Premier Konoye, Japan’s view regarding Pacific
                            problems which are pending between Japan and the United States.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
